b166e188-b6dd-49a7-a6ce-9a8233d9e5f3.049ae41b-9f4f-4666-909e-26c2df078985.description=
Adds a flow variable into the local context (available to itself and child flows only)

Input Parameters\:
keyName - the name of the flow variable to use
myValue - the value to assign the flow variable

Responses\:
success - assigned the flow variable

Scriptlet Example\:
[$scriptletContext putGlobal\: $keyName, $myValue];
b166e188-b6dd-49a7-a6ce-9a8233d9e5f3.63ae3e36-3227-4960-aec9-253c8bb469e5.description=
Adds two numbers together

Inputs\:
value1 - the first value.
value2 - the second value.

Returns\:
The sum of the two numbers.

Responses\:
success - The operation completed successfully.
failure - Something went wrong.
b166e188-b6dd-49a7-a6ce-9a8233d9e5f3.90426d10-77e0-4bf8-bbbc-a81736902607.description=Performs a mathematical operation on two numbers or strings Inputs\: operator - The operation to perform (+ - * ^ / > < \=\= \!\= >\= <\=). value1 - the first value. value2 - the second value. Returns\: The result of the operation, for boolean values this is true or false. Responses\: success - The operation completed successfully. If a boolean operation, it evaluated to true. failure - Something went wrong or the boolean operation returned false. b166e188-b6dd-49a7-a6ce-9a8233d9e5f3.991d92d0-36a8-4e63-aa86-997f1f852600.description=Check to see if the value stored in a specified key is null. Inputs\: keyName - the key to check Returns\: The value in the specified key. Responses\: isNull - if the key is a null pointer. notNull - if some value is stored in the key. b166e188-b6dd-49a7-a6ce-9a8233d9e5f3.bbcb1f1a-a977-4d3e-997e-ee6c99cc9a19.callout=Can be used to get a value from a list that is at the same position in the list as an element in another list. This can be used to map between two lists. b166e188-b6dd-49a7-a6ce-9a8233d9e5f3.c93a903c-8187-4c85-8976-8c896b675e81.description=
This is an operation that does nothing, and can be used to display information to the user by editing the display tab. It can also be used for filtering flow variables by feeding them in as inputs, and filtering them on the results tab.

Inputs\:
field1 - optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
field2 - optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
field3 - optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
field4 - optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.

Responses\:
success - this operation never fails.
b166e188-b6dd-49a7-a6ce-9a8233d9e5f3.description=\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\# \#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\# \# General Information \# 
Description\:
	Can be used to get a value from a list that is at the same position in the list as an element in another list. This can be
	used to map between two lists.
Inputs\:
	keyList		The list of keys, The flow will map from this list.
	valueList		The list of values that correspond to the keys. This list must have the same length at keyList.
	key		The value of the key to lookup.
	delimiter		The delimiter for keyList and valueList.
Responses\:
	success		The key was found.
	failure		the key was not found or something went wrong.
Returns\:
	value		The value that corresponds to the given key.
	index		The index where the key was found.
Notes\:
	N/A

If the list changes while running, the updates will be appended to the list. Inputs\: list - The list to iterate through. separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the list. Returns\: The current element of the list, if the response is has more Responses\: has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned. has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list. failure - failed to process the list. Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously. WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration.. b166e188-b6dd-49a7-a6ce-9a8233d9e5f3.fcae459c-4acf-491d-8264-41981d61736b.description=Iterates through a list of values. Returns\: The current element of the list, if the response is has more Responses\: has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned. has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list. failure - failed to process the list. Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously. WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration..
